    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix invalid memory access in send_standalone_dummy function\n\n### Summary\nThe `send_standalone_dummy` function in the PHY stub UE implementation was sending raw binary data instead of a properly formatted NFAPI message. This caused invalid memory access and segmentation faults when the receiving end attempted to unpack the message.\n\nThe issue occurred when no UL indication messages were generated during a subframe processing cycle, triggering the dummy message send path. The raw data `{0, 0}` was not a valid NFAPI message structure, causing the receiver to attempt parsing at invalid memory locations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/PHY_INTERFACE/phy_stub_UE.c`: Modified `send_standalone_dummy()` to send a properly formatted empty NFAPI RX_INDICATION message instead of raw binary data.\n\nUnder high load conditions with frequent dummy message sends, this bug caused intermittent crashes in the standalone PNF processing thread. The fix ensures dummy messages follow the same NFAPI formatting as other indication messages, preventing memory access violations.\n"
}